## Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js application.

### Changes Made:

**1. Installed Dependencies:**
   - Added `@vercel/speed-insights` package via npm
   - Updated `package.json` with the new dependency
   - Updated `package-lock.json` to reflect the installation

**2. Modified Files:**
   - `app/layout.tsx`:
     - Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
     - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after `{children}`

### Implementation Details:

This project uses Next.js 16.1.1 with the App Router, which is version 13.5+. Therefore, I used the recommended approach:
- Imported `SpeedInsights` from `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Added the component to the root layout file (`app/layout.tsx`)
- Placed it inside the `<body>` tag after the children, which is the recommended location

### Verification:

✓ Linter passed with no errors (`npm run lint`)
✓ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✓ No test suite available (no test script configured)
✓ All changes preserve existing code structure and functionality

The Speed Insights component will now automatically track and report Web Vitals metrics for the application when deployed to Vercel.
